---
import ExternalLink from "../components/ExternalLink.astro"
import GetExtensionBadges from "../components/GetExtensionBadges.astro"
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout title="About">
  <div class="bg"></div>
  <section class="get-smc">
    <h1>StopMalwareContent</h1>
    <p>Restricts access to harmful or potentionally unwanted websites.</p>
    <GetExtensionBadges />
  </section>
  <section class="why-smc">
    <h2>Why StopMalwareContent?</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="lucide lucide-github"
            ><path
              d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"
            ></path><path d="M9 18c-4.51 2-5-2-7-2"></path></svg
          >
        </div>
        <span class="title">It's free and open source</span>
        <span class="description"
          >All source code of our extension is publically available on GitHub!</span
        >
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="lucide lucide-users"
            ><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path><circle
              cx="9"
              cy="7"
              r="4"></circle><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path><path
              d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path></svg
          >
        </div>
        <span class="title">Powered by community</span>
        <span class="description"
          >Our contributors working hard too! That's power of open source!</span
        >
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="icon">
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="lucide lucide-bar-chart-3"
            ><path d="M3 3v18h18"></path><path d="M18 17V9"></path><path
              d="M13 17V5"></path><path d="M8 17v-3"></path></svg
          >
        </div>
        <span class="title">Actively maintained</span>
        <span class="description"
          >We're working hard on imporving and updating our extension!</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="about-smc">
    <h2>About StopMalwareContent</h2>
    <p>
      A StopMalwareContent browser extension, as the name suggests stops malware
      content by preventing you the user form visiting malicious and potentially
      unwanted websites (PUWs).
    </p>
    <p>
      What are malicious and potentially unwanted websites? Malicious websites
      it's a websites that directly promote malware, or try to steal your
      credentials (phishing websites) or perform any other illegal activities.
      But potentially unwanted websites are different, they may not try to
      directly throw viruses at you, but they may try to promote their adware
      extension for example! Remember websites that try to install their
      suspicious search engine? We flag them as potentially unwanted, as they
      may not directly harm your computer. However we also block websites with
      specific reasons, for example we can block specific URLs, like GitHub
      repositories that contain viruses, or other example, we can block specific
      YouTube video that promotes malicious content.
    </p>
    <p>
      We made this all for your privacy and safety. About privacy, we don't
      store your personal information or track websites that you visit, we only
      gather information like your browser, operating system, etc. with purpose
      of analyzing and improving our services.
    </p>
    <p>
      StopMalwareContent is completely free and open source, licensed under GNU
      General Public License v3.0 license. Visit our GitHub repository to learn
      more:
      <ExternalLink to="https://github.com/StopMalwareContent/Extension"
        >https://github.com/StopMalwareContent/Extension</ExternalLink
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  body {
    height: 100% !important;
  }

  .bg {
    position: absolute;
    z-index: -10;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #0f0f0f, var(--primary));
    background-size: 100% 100%;
    animation: gradient 1300ms cubic-bezier(0.455, 0.03, 0.515, 0.955);
  }

  @keyframes gradient {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
      background-size: 100% 1000%;
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 1;
      background-size: 100% 100%;
    }
  }

  .get-smc {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: calc(100% + 0.3em);

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
  }

  .why-smc {
    .cards {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.3em;
      margin-top: 1em;

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        flex-direction: column;
        height: 400px;
      }
    }
    .card {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
      border-radius: 5px;
      padding: 1em;
      text-align: center;
      width: 100%;
      height: 200px;

      .icon svg {
        width: 3em;
        height: 3em;
      }

      .title {
        font-size: 1.2em;
        font-weight: bold;
      }
    }
  }

  .about-smc {
    p {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
  }

  section {
    &:not(:last-child) {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--primary);
    }
    padding: 5em 0;
  }
</style>
